title: PML-N’s Malik Laal Muhammad wins PP-224 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 09 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz’s (PML-N) Malik Laal Muhammad has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-224 Multan-XII by securing 44,264 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Muhammad Abbas Bukhari, an independent candidate who bagged 28,433 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 50.55%.
